00:21:08,079 --> 00:21:09,519
Then you will do that job well.

284
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,559
Mom.

285
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:18,599
-What is it?
-What?

286
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,440
-What's going on?
-I'm touched.

287
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:21,839
-Touched?
-Gen.

288
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:24,359
I thought you wanted to wipe your mouth.

289
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,359
-Here.
-Come on.

290
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,880
Our little puppy.

291
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:30,079
Puppies come from dogs.

292
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,559
-That backfired.
-Look at him.

293
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,119
You're never like this.

294
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:36,400
-Come on.
-Okay, you're touched.

295
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:38,480
I love you too.

296
00:21:38,559 --> 00:21:40,160
-Can I hug you?
-Come here.

297
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:42,799
You little puppy.

298
00:21:44,119 --> 00:21:45,880
Had Nut had a warm

299
00:21:46,359 --> 00:21:48,000
and understanding family,

300
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:53,839
he would've grown up to be
a happy young man like Gen.

301
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:03,279
THE LITTLE PRINCE

302
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,240
You're home.

303
00:22:11,799 --> 00:22:12,880
What's wrong?

304
00:22:14,039 --> 00:22:15,440
Can you tell me?

305
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:52,599
SONG: SLEEPING ALONE
MUST BE LONELY, MISTER

306
00:23:56,799 --> 00:23:59,119
I'M NOT LONELY

307
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:05,000
I HAVE SOMEONE TO SLEEP WITH

308
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:18,839
Gen.

309
00:24:19,319 --> 00:24:20,599
What?

310
00:24:21,559 --> 00:24:23,160
Will I get to live with Nut again?

311
00:24:27,079 --> 00:24:28,200
I don't know.

312
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,079
You and Nut are the only ones who know.

313
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:34,759
It's up to your hearts

314
00:24:35,319 --> 00:24:36,880
if you want to get back together.

315
00:24:39,039 --> 00:24:40,759
I really want to.

316
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,000
But…

317
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:48,359
Nut…

318
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:51,640
Stop sulking.

319
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,279
Nut is just confused.

320
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:58,160
It's hard for him to move on

321
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:00,519
and start over, you know?

322
00:25:03,799 --> 00:25:06,559
He probably had high hopes,

323
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:09,960
and you must have disappointed him.

324
00:25:10,839 --> 00:25:12,200
Give him time.

325
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,440
I'll talk to him.

326
00:25:32,119 --> 00:25:35,480
SONG: WHO? WHO ARE YOU SLEEPING WITH?

327
00:25:35,559 --> 00:25:38,759
ARE YOU CHEATING ON ME?

328
00:25:38,839 --> 00:25:44,880
MISTER, DON'T

329
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,039
Nut.

330
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:50,480
I want to be back by your side.

331
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:54,079
I will not give up.

332
00:26:02,279 --> 00:26:04,279
BE WITH YOU

333
00:26:06,039 --> 00:26:06,880
Wait.

334
00:26:08,039 --> 00:26:09,160
You're not Neung.

335
00:26:09,839 --> 00:26:11,640
Isn't he your friend?

336
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:15,680
He fell from your balcony
yesterday morning.

337
00:26:34,039 --> 00:26:35,759
Who gave you that pork recipe?

338
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,000
I just followed my gut.

339
00:26:49,599 --> 00:26:51,519
I'm your teddy bear.

340
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,720
I'm your teddy bear.

341
00:28:38,319 --> 00:28:39,160
But…

342
00:28:40,119 --> 00:28:41,480
I have no idea

343
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,200
how I turned into a human.

344
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:48,440
Do you really think Tofu is a teddy bear?

345
00:28:49,359 --> 00:28:50,759
Who would be that crazy?

346
00:28:52,519 --> 00:28:54,759
I just thought it might have
something to do with…

347
00:28:55,319 --> 00:28:56,920
Is this about your ex again?

348
00:28:59,519 --> 00:29:02,119
Do you think your ex revolves around you

349
00:29:02,799 --> 00:29:04,599
like a planet orbiting around the sun?

350
00:29:07,039 --> 00:29:08,599
I'm not just imagining it.

351
00:29:09,319 --> 00:29:10,880
I have my reasons.

352
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:15,160
Tofu reminds me of him all the time.

353
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:20,000
Nut, there are tens of millions of people
in this country.

354
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:22,960
Don't you think
some of them talk and think alike?

355
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:26,799
Tofu could've watched the same movies,

356
00:29:27,279 --> 00:29:28,680
read the same books,

357
00:29:28,759 --> 00:29:31,480
and listened to the same songs as your ex.

358
00:29:32,119 --> 00:29:33,319
That's why he said that.

359
00:29:34,319 --> 00:29:36,079
But what he said was special.

360
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,279
He used the exact same words.

361
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,319
So what?

362
00:29:41,119 --> 00:29:43,880
Did you think he sent Tofu here
to steal your teddy bear,

363
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,119
say those lines,

364
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:48,559
and love you in his place?

365
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:55,279
If you can't answer it,

366
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:59,079
why bother thinking about
impossible questions like that?

367
00:29:59,759 --> 00:30:02,279
You should think about the question
that you can answer.

368
00:30:03,359 --> 00:30:05,720
Do you still want Tofu in your life?

369
00:30:38,759 --> 00:30:40,559
So it's you

370
00:30:41,319 --> 00:30:42,359
who was with him.

371
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:47,200
Why do you need to borrow my laptop?

372
00:30:47,839 --> 00:30:48,759
To get Nut back.

373
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:20,119
I'M NOT LONELY WITHOUT YOU

374
00:31:23,359 --> 00:31:24,680
Why did you go to my house?

375
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:29,440
Where are you taking Tofu?

376
00:31:34,359 --> 00:31:35,200
Here.

377
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,319
I guess that's love.

378
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:43,480
Even though he kicked you out,

379
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,279
you still look after his mom.

380
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,720
I promised Nut

381
00:31:50,519 --> 00:31:52,119
that I would take care of her.

382
00:31:54,039 --> 00:31:55,640
Even if he's still mad at me,

383
00:31:56,599 --> 00:31:58,279
I need to keep my promise.

384
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:00,839
True love.

385
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,240
I'm going now.

386
00:32:05,319 --> 00:32:06,599
Okay.

387
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:18,160
-Look, Tofu is here.
-Tofu.

388
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:20,640
-Tofu is here.
-Tofu.

389
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:22,119
What a relief.

390
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:25,359
I was praying for your safety all night.

391
00:32:27,599 --> 00:32:30,519
What about Ms. Left Slipper?

392
00:32:44,759 --> 00:32:46,880
Why did you come back alone?

393
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:51,400
Mr. Right Slipper,
where's your girlfriend?

394
00:32:53,599 --> 00:32:56,240
I lost Ms. Left Slipper.

395
00:32:58,079 --> 00:32:58,920
What?

396
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:00,640
My goodness.

397
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:03,519
Little One shouldn't have helped you.

398
00:33:03,599 --> 00:33:06,480
You always call others ignorant.

399
00:33:07,039 --> 00:33:09,720
Well, your girlfriend
can't ignore you now.

400
00:33:16,960 --> 00:33:18,680
I promise you, Mr. Right Slipper,

401
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,480
I'll find Little One.

402
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:24,720
I would never lose Mrs. Na's belongings.

403
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,200
Where's Mrs. Na?

404
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,280
Oh…

405
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,039
Thank you.

406
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:53,360
Let me help.

407
00:35:04,079 --> 00:35:06,400
It wouldn't be as pretty
had I done it myself.

408
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:09,400
Thank you for helping me.

409
00:35:10,599 --> 00:35:11,800
You're welcome.

410
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:23,159
This area still seems a bit bare.

411
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:26,639
Shall we buy some more plants?

412
00:35:30,119 --> 00:35:31,400
Are you free this Saturday?

413
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:38,880
Let's take a photo

414
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:44,400
as a memento of the three of us
arranging the garden together.

415
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,599
I'll put the chair away.

416
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,280
Let me help.

417
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:52,639
I need to research a lot
for the subject I teach,

418
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:55,320
in order to explain it to the children.

419
00:36:58,719 --> 00:37:00,800
But the more I research,

420
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:02,800
the more questions I have.

421
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,360
Do you think

422
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:09,519
Thai people really did migrate
from the Altai Mountains?

423
00:37:11,559 --> 00:37:13,320
And did the villagers of Bang Rachan

424
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:17,480
really die fighting to protect Ayutthaya?

425
00:37:19,719 --> 00:37:20,800
So,

426
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,159
is it not true?

427
00:37:26,519 --> 00:37:27,360
Well,

428
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,719
I don't know much about this stuff.

429
00:37:30,639 --> 00:37:33,880
You might have to explain it to me
a bit more.

430
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:39,440
Would you mind

431
00:37:40,039 --> 00:37:42,599
if I asked you to come
and explain it to me every day?

432
00:37:47,079 --> 00:37:48,719
Maybe Thais didn't migrate here

433
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,880
but have always been in this area.

434
00:37:52,679 --> 00:37:56,639
As for Bang Rachan, they didn't fight
for anyone but themselves.

435
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,280
Is that what you think?

436
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:06,199
History isn't a record
of what actually happened.

437
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:10,159
It's just distorted recollections

438
00:38:11,119 --> 00:38:14,760
that are retold in a way
that suits whoever is telling them.

439
00:38:15,559 --> 00:38:16,679
Do you agree?

440
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:20,960
I didn't think…

441
00:38:22,519 --> 00:38:24,480
you would be interested in history.

442
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:27,119
I like to read.

443
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:31,360
History, philosophy, and literature.

444
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:34,480
This one

445
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:36,880
is my favorite.

446
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:37,960
THE LITTLE PRINCE

447
00:38:38,039 --> 00:38:39,280
"The Little Prince."

448
00:38:41,719 --> 00:38:44,000
I really like
the illustrations in this book.

449
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,719
But when I was at school,

450
00:38:47,719 --> 00:38:49,679
I didn't really understand it.

451
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:52,440
They say,

452
00:38:52,519 --> 00:38:55,760
older people perceive
The Little Prince differently

453
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:58,199
than children.

454
00:38:59,119 --> 00:39:01,559
You should read it again.

455
00:39:01,639 --> 00:39:04,599
You might understand
and perceive it differently this time.

456
00:39:07,079 --> 00:39:08,039
Okay.

457
00:39:20,639 --> 00:39:22,079
Sib.

458
00:39:26,920 --> 00:39:28,000
Mrs. Na.

459
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:32,840
When did you get here, Tofu?

460
00:39:34,599 --> 00:39:35,920
Just now.

461
00:39:37,599 --> 00:39:39,719
Do you remember Mr. Sibmeun now?

462
00:39:45,679 --> 00:39:47,519
Do you want to tell me anything?

463
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:57,599
-Thank you.
-It's okay.

464
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:09,440
You all look happy in this picture.

465
00:40:10,679 --> 00:40:12,920
Why don't you want to think about it?

466
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:18,280
Sometimes you are happy

467
00:40:19,519 --> 00:40:22,159
at the start of a nightmare, Tofu.

468
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:28,559
We can't have good dreams all the time.

469
00:40:31,599 --> 00:40:33,639
I have a secret to tell you.

470
00:40:33,719 --> 00:40:35,559
You're the first one to know.

471
00:40:43,199 --> 00:40:45,519
I've just started dreaming recently.

472
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,320
Whenever I have a nightmare,

473
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:51,519
I would really be glad when I wake up,

474
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:54,320
because I know it's just a dream.

475
00:40:55,119 --> 00:40:56,079
It has passed.

476
00:40:56,639 --> 00:40:58,920
The monster in my dream
can't hurt me anymore.

477
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,880
Whenever I have a good dream,

478
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,000
I'm happy all day long.

479
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:10,840
Don't you want

480
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:13,079
to go back to sleep

481
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:15,280
to continue the good dream?

482
00:41:16,960 --> 00:41:18,119
No.

483
00:41:19,119 --> 00:41:20,760
In my real life, I have Nut,

484
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:23,239
you,

485
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:25,960
and many other friends.

486
00:41:27,079 --> 00:41:29,159
Sometimes I'm happy. Sometimes I'm sad.

487
00:41:30,599 --> 00:41:32,280
But it's reality.

488
00:41:33,559 --> 00:41:35,519
I wouldn't trade it for a dream.

489
00:41:58,280 --> 00:41:59,360
Mrs. Na.

490
00:42:01,039 --> 00:42:02,840
Some nights you have good dreams.

491
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,800
Some nights you have bad dreams.

492
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,400
But in the end,

493
00:42:10,639 --> 00:42:12,719
you have to wake up.

494
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:46,519
I've decided

495
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:49,280
to borrow some money
from Sakon to help Na.

496
00:42:51,639 --> 00:42:53,280
Have you thought it through?

497
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:54,599
She's struggling.

498
00:42:55,079 --> 00:42:58,000
She has to pay for her house
and her grandmother's medical bills.

499
00:42:58,079 --> 00:42:59,000
What can I do?

500
00:42:59,079 --> 00:43:00,519
It's pointless.

501
00:43:00,599 --> 00:43:02,559
You won't hold her grandmother back.

502
00:43:02,639 --> 00:43:05,079
It will just prolong her suffering.

503
00:43:05,639 --> 00:43:08,719
In the end,
the person who will suffer the most is Na.

504
00:43:10,280 --> 00:43:12,280
Is it Na or you who will suffer?

505
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:15,960
Do you think I don't know
what you're trying to do?

506
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:20,320
Is it only a soldier with a bright future
like you who deserves Na?

507
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:23,679
When we were kids, I may not have been
as good as you at anything,

508
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:27,440
but I won't let you
walk all over me this time.

509
00:43:28,199 --> 00:43:29,920
You know Na loves me.

510
00:43:32,679 --> 00:43:34,599
I'm warning you with good intentions.

511
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:38,679
Think it through.
The money will cause you trouble.

512
00:43:40,920 --> 00:43:42,239
I have thought it through.

513
00:43:42,960 --> 00:43:44,960
I will show both you and Na

514
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:47,679
that I can make her happy too.

515
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:12,639
May I give him a sponge bath?

516
00:44:12,719 --> 00:44:13,559
Go ahead.

517
00:45:49,639 --> 00:45:51,239
The lab results are in.

518
00:45:51,719 --> 00:45:54,280
We found a bloodstain
on the living room floor,

519
00:45:54,760 --> 00:45:56,320
but it had been cleaned.

520
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:58,840
That means a fight occurred here.

521
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:01,440
I think Tatarn

522
00:46:01,519 --> 00:46:04,360
could have been injured and moved.

523
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:07,400
So, it seems like
he was attacked and killed.

524
00:46:07,480 --> 00:46:09,239
That means Saen lied to us.

525
00:46:12,039 --> 00:46:13,800
Should we issue a warrant?

526
00:46:15,039 --> 00:46:17,199
Not yet. Don't alert him.

527
00:46:18,239 --> 00:46:22,960
He went this far to deceive us.
He and his wife must have a solid plan.

528
00:46:24,199 --> 00:46:26,400
Find some solid evidence against him,

529
00:46:26,920 --> 00:46:28,360
then we'll arrest him.

530
00:46:40,119 --> 00:46:41,360
Lieutenant.

531
00:46:41,920 --> 00:46:43,400
Have a look around.

532
00:46:43,480 --> 00:46:45,119
There must be more evidence.

533
00:46:45,199 --> 00:46:46,360
Yes, sir.

534
00:46:55,599 --> 00:46:58,199
Do you remember what I told you?

535
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:00,480
About someone Tarn liked.

536
00:47:02,960 --> 00:47:04,079
I do.

537
00:47:04,159 --> 00:47:07,360
I would ask permission
to enter Tarn's house

538
00:47:07,920 --> 00:47:10,280
to find clues about this person.

539
00:47:12,719 --> 00:47:14,679
I want to create a miracle.

540
00:47:19,039 --> 00:47:22,119
TO NUT, FROM TOFU

541
00:48:03,159 --> 00:48:04,440
Excuse me, sir.

542
00:48:04,519 --> 00:48:05,400
It's the commander.

543
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:08,800
Yes.

544
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:10,559
Roger that.

545
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:30,280
"Be with you."

546
00:49:30,360 --> 00:49:32,320
BE WITH YOU

547
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:33,880
What are you doing?

548
00:49:37,880 --> 00:49:39,280
I'm not doing anything.

549
00:49:39,800 --> 00:49:41,239
I'm just arranging your books.

550
00:49:43,519 --> 00:49:44,800
Why this book?

551
00:49:45,960 --> 00:49:47,320
Well?

552
00:49:54,239 --> 00:49:55,079
And this.

553
00:49:56,239 --> 00:49:59,079
You hid the teddy's scarf
in my room, didn't you?

554
00:50:00,239 --> 00:50:01,280
Didn't you?

555
00:50:03,679 --> 00:50:04,800
I didn't.

556
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:08,440
It had fallen, so I put it away.

557
00:50:09,239 --> 00:50:10,440
Don't lie!

558
00:50:11,719 --> 00:50:13,760
You were going through my personal stuff!

559
00:50:14,480 --> 00:50:15,480
